# NanoClaw + Mnemon — same orchestrator as the plain `nanoclaw` environment,
# containerized only (no host/systemd/launchd mode — see the README), with
# github.com/mnemon-dev/mnemon patched into NanoClaw's own agent sandbox for
# persistent, cross-session memory. Fully independent of the plain `nanoclaw`
# environment: separate install path, separate container name, separate port
# — both can be deployed on the same machine without colliding. The
# Anthropic API key is registered interactively by nanoclaw.sh on first
# install.

# The orchestrator container's name. Kept distinct from the plain nanoclaw
# environment's ("nanoclaw") so both can run on the same machine.
CONTAINER_NAME=nanoclaw-mnemon

# Absolute path where the nanoclaw repo will be cloned and installed. Kept
# distinct from the plain nanoclaw environment's default so the two never
# share (or silently corrupt) each other's data if both are deployed on the
# same machine.
# Format: An absolute path where the current user has write access. This is
# bind-mounted into the orchestrator container at the SAME absolute path
# (not remapped to something else) — required so the orchestrator can
# correctly spawn per-conversation-group agent containers via the host's
# Docker socket. See the README's "Deployment Modes" section before
# changing how this is mounted.
NANOCLAW_INSTALL_PATH=/home/pi/nanoclaw-mnemon

# The port exposed by the NanoClaw web interface for browser-based
# conversations. Kept distinct from the plain nanoclaw environment's
# default (3080) so both can run on the same machine at once.
# Format: A valid local TCP port number.
NANOCLAW_PORT=3081

# The mnemon release version to install into NanoClaw's agent sandbox image
# — see https://github.com/mnemon-dev/mnemon/releases. Pinned rather than
# "latest" so a CLEAN redeploy doesn't silently pick up a new mnemon release
# without you choosing to.
# Format: A mnemon release tag without the leading "v" (e.g. 0.1.1).
MNEMON_VERSION=0.1.1

# Optional — enables mnemon's own built-in hybrid graph+vector recall
# (mnemon's own MNEMON_EMBED_ENDPOINT, not something this environment
# invented). Left unset, mnemon runs graph-only, which is its own
# documented default — not a degraded mode. Uncomment to enable; on
# Docker Desktop, host.docker.internal reaches whatever Ollama you have
# running on the host itself. If set, run.sh's ensure_ollama_ready()
# checks whether that endpoint is reachable and — only for a local
# address (host.docker.internal/localhost/127.0.0.1) — offers to install
# Ollama via Homebrew (macOS) or the official installer (Linux), starts
# it if it's installed but not running, and pulls the model if missing.
# Installation always asks for confirmation first; every failure here is
# a warning, never a hard stop — the rest of the deploy proceeds either
# way, with mnemon just running graph-only until this resolves.
# Requires a CLEAN redeploy to take effect on an already-deployed install
# (same as bumping MNEMON_VERSION above — the patch only applies to a
# fresh clone).
# Format: A URL mnemon's container can reach.
# MNEMON_EMBED_ENDPOINT=http://host.docker.internal:11434

# Optional — overrides mnemon's own default embedding model
# (nomic-embed-text). Only read if MNEMON_EMBED_ENDPOINT above is set.
# Format: An Ollama model name already pulled on that endpoint's daemon.
# MNEMON_EMBED_MODEL=nomic-embed-text
